[00:23.44]One such cause now seeks to end biomedical research
[00:29.10]because of the theory that animals have rights ruling out their use in research.
[00:35.57]Scientists need to respond forcefully to animal rights advocates,
[00:42.80]whose arguments are confusing the public and thereby threatening advances in health knowledge and care.
[00:49.98]Leaders of the animal rights movement target biomedical research because it depends on public funding,
[00:58.61]and few people understand the process of health care research.
[01:03.60]Hearing allegations of cruelty to animals in research settings,
[01:08.94]many are perplexed that anyone would deliberately harm an animal.
[01:14.13]For example, a grandmotherly woman staffing an animal rights booth
[01:21.16]at a recent street fair was distributing a brochure
